  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a hardware/physical mismatch (Category B): iter_1 pays most time in startup by deserializing and touching cache-exceeding posting indexes (notably num_adsh_tag_version_hash) and rebuilding tag lookup state, so performance is dominated by memory traffic before useful filtering. The revised plan removes those large index-driven probes and uses a fused sequential num scan with early selective filters plus two compact cache-friendlier hash structures: a pre(stmt='EQ') triple semi-join set and a tag(tag,version)->tlabel map, with sub SIC filtering applied first via dense lookup. This shifts work to sequential access and proportional hash probes, reducing wasted startup work and random-access pressure.",
